node.text:
I’ve wanted to make this post for awhile but I’ve been overwhelmed how to start “out of no where”. I don’t feel comfortable trying to educate but the least I can do is give a spotlight.
My Indian name is Wab Anug, Morning Star this means the morning sun that rises in the East and I am of Anishinaabe Métis decent. (This makes me giggle because everyone who knows me, knows I will always be the first to stay up or get up) I was born and live on Treaty One Territory (Winnipeg, Manitoba) home of the Anishinaabe, Métis, Cree, Dakota, Dene and Oji-Cree peoples. 
Today is #NationalIndigenousPeoplesDay 🧡 in Canada and I want to take a step forward in acknowledging my Métis background and will do more to educate myself about Indigenous Peoples. The painful history and treatment of Indigenous Peoples need to be brought forward and talked about in the mainstream. These issues cannot be swept under the rug any longer. Similarly, I've always known of my background, but like many others from my generation, my Métis background was rarely talked about. Recently, I've obtained a copy of my family tree and my ancestors played instrumental roles in laying the groundwork for the Métis. I won't be able to make the same impact that they left, but I want to do my part to educate myself.
The treatment of Indigenous Peoples, not only in Canada but the many other countries where colonization took place needs to be brought to light. The effects of colonization creates intergenerational trauma and our people need to continue to seek safe spaces and allies to talk with to help heal from the past. We have come a long way but there is still way too much to be desired.
You need to know where you came from in order to find yourself. Life is always about learning and knowing your history will help shape the future you want to have.
I hope that this post inspires you to not look the other way when these difficult topics come up. If you don't understand, ask someone and if you don't understand something that is okay.. that’s what #youtube is for lol.. and I’ve linked some short videos to help give a starting point to get some ideas topics that need to be talked about. Please repost 💞🥰

node.text:
it’s been off here for 3 months. First of all.. every message and DM of y’all being worried for me and sending me all the love, strength even prayers.. all get absorbed into my soul and I’m forever thankful. I’ve never been able to show you guys my darkest moments in life but I’m out here trying to make the right steps and dealing with change. Not just with my dog of 15 years leaving me but just getting older as a bad bitch and learning to embrace that my life is restarting yet again, I’ve learned the tools already to be fearless so that’s what I am focusing on.
These past months has made me become very anti-social and just living in the moment. But as time goes by and I become more disconnected with being online, it feels like I’m now the odd one out. My break was amazing and I’m still healing but you know what, I am beautifully broken and I’m sure many of y’all can relate and THATS OKAY!!! 
Living in Canada has been pretty rough w/ all of our lockdowns (My city is still partially shut down for the THIRD time) and watching the rest of the world live their best life is just so wild haha... being with myself has made me pay attention to some negative things about myself.. So I am working on having better thoughts about myself, which I think we could all work on!! SoooooOooo at this point... I just want some of your attention already!!! 😂 LOL so I love you and I’ve missed you ALL!!! I want to see you all in real life soon 😘 *photo dump

node.text:
No longer by my side.... but Forever in my Heart R.I.P my lil man🥺
I’ve spent the past years dedicated to Ares every move.. since his second eye was removed I literally have been his eyes, his legs, his everything. He has been my everything.
I’ve adjusted my whole life for him so today I am waking up completely hallow. I basically sleep with one eye open incase he cries or pees or wakes up I can tend to him. I know this was going to be hard but I honestly didn’t think I would be this sad since I’ve had time to prepare for his departure.
He went out eating, in my arms in the comfort of our home and that’s the way to do it, right?!
My eyes have been sore for the past weeks and I know only time will help heal this... 15 years is a long time, he’s the extension of me.. I just need to keep reminding myself all the sunshine this little guy brought me.
I can’t thank you all enough for all the heart filled messages 😭 I’ve literally read them all and keep telling my family how much these msgs have been helping me cope to not feel alone and so grateful how much you all love Ares and are concerned for me.
🐶I’ll miss you so much each and everyday just like I do your brother and sister. 
Thank you @allypapkophotography for capturing these *precious moments ❤️
